Priscilla Osaje Mr Ideh Chukwuma Innocent, producer of a blockbuster movie ‘ Pillars of Africa’ has announced the release of the film across cinemas  scheduled for July 23. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the film, which is finally set to hit cinema screen has been on production for three years. Innocent, who doubles as the producer/director  said that  movie tells the story of  a Republic called “Izambi”. He wrote on his instagram; “@hakeemkaekazim plays the role of captain Otega. The leader of the rabel group in the movie PILLARS OF AFRICA. He gave a world class super performance. Brought to you by @silverbirddistribution showing in all cinema across Nigeria and beyond!!!. Brace yourself cc @naijaonnetflix @netflixfilm @filmoneng @genesiscinemas@bluepicturesng#pillarsofafricathemovie #filmmaking#comingsoon#cinema,” he wrote. The movie tells the story of the African child and their struggle in surviving here in Africa, in a war broken country called ‘IZAMBI REPUBLIC’. The rebel leader kidnapped and transport innocent children (girls) into his slave camp where they would be used as sex slaves. ‘Pillars of Africa’ featured movie stars in Hollywood and Nollywood actors like Hakeem Kae Kazim, Sola Sobowale, Chidi Mokeme, Segun Arinze, Zack Orji, Sam Dede, Elvina Ibru. He  said the movie offered a great opportunity for young actors like Bukky Okorodus, Bryan Okoye, George Nanakwesi, Ian Wordi, Mor Okonkwo, Micheal Sunny, among others. Innocent also known as ‘ONESOUL’ is one of nollywood’s fresh brain, with so many great movies to his credit. (NAN) Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related